column2:
Cinder-breath glides on rails of glass, a hissed heartbeat in chrome armor;
A sentinel of sunrise, it hums a route through paved rivers, drinking light.
Leather sighs under map-light stars, while rubber feet kiss the edge of miles;
It bears a chorus of bells and hurry, a private storm tucked behind a windshield pause.
Motion wears a blanket of scent—tar, rain, and distant gasoline prayers.
Its shadow stretches, tires tapping like rain on a metálico drum.
